title: Live: Two-judge bench to hear Pilot camp's amended petition today
description: The Congress has made several overtures to Sachin Pilot, indicating that the party is keen to keep him within the fold. On Thursday, Pilot and other rebel MLAs moved Rajasthan HC, challenging the Assembly Speaker's disqualification notice. Stay with TOI for all the updates

title: 'PM taking inputs from top officials on economy'
description: Prime Minister Modi is meeting top officials of the finance and commerce ministries later on Thursday to assess the impact of ongoing COVID-19 pandemic on the national economy, official sources said. According to sources, the Prime Minister is taking inputs from top 50 officials. They said the Prime Minister's focus will be on speedy recovery of the economy.

title: ‘More flights, lower fares to & from west soon’
description: There will soon be more flights — at lower fares — to the US, UK and some EU nations. India has established "air bubbles" with the US, France and Germany and is in "advanced stage talks" with the UK for the same, the aviation ministry said on Thursday. Air India has decided to lower fares of its Vande Bharat Mission flights to these countries.

title: Part of building crashes in south Mumbai
description: A portion of the Bhanushali building on Mint Road in Fort area collapsed during heavy rain. Following the incident, fire brigade personnel and members of disaster management team rushed to the spot and started removing debris to locate missing people.

title: 'Will comment after report from officials on Jadhav'
Disengagement process needs verification: Army
description: The process of complete disengagement of troops in eastern Ladakh is "intricate" and requires constant verification, the Indian Army said on Thursday after the fourth round of marathon military talks between India and China. ​​The army said senior commanders of the Indian and Chinese military reviewed the progress on implementation of the first phase of disengagement and discussed further steps to ensure complete withdrawal of troops in the region.

title: BB 13's Koena Mitra files FIR against imposter
description: Actress Koena Mitra, who created quite a stir pertaining to her headstrong personality in the Bigg Boss 13 house and is quite vocal about her thoughts, has filed a police complaint against an imposter who's running an Instagram account under her name.

title: Odisha govt reveals support given to Dutee Chand
description: A day sprinter Dutee Chand issued a clarification saying she isn't selling her car to raise training funds, Odisha government revealed that a total of Rs 4.09 crore has been given to Dutee since 2015. It was reported that Dutee, who put up a now-deleted FB post asking buyers to get in touch with her manager, was forced to sell her car to raise funds for her Olympics training.

title: Cost cutting is needed: Puri on AI leave w/o pay
description: Equity infusion of Rs 500-600 crore every year is not sustainable and cost-cutting in Air India is necessary, Hardeep Singh Puri said on Thursday, justifying AI's decision to send certain employees on leave without pay for up to 5 years. His remarks came after TMC MP Derek O'Brien slammed Air India, saying its leave-without-pay scheme violates labour laws.

title: How Chinese brands face the first real 'Desi' threat
How Vivo X50 Pro compares with rival phones
'Not sure if recovered Covid patients lose immunity'
description: Recent studies suggest that those recovering from Covid-19 may have antibodies for only a few months, a signal that long-term immunity is difficult to achieve, but several scientists dispel the gloom and say it is too soon to determine if such individuals can contract the disease again. Some special cells of the immune system may still offer protection against the disease.

title: Nissan unveils Magnite SUV concept, to rival Venue
description: Japanese carmakers Nissan on Thursday unveiled the B-segment Magnite SUV concept. Nissan Magnite will go on sale later in FY20-21, competing with the likes of Hyundai Venue, upcoming Kia Sonet, Maruti Suzuki Vitara Brezza, Tata Nexon, Mahindra XUV300 and Ford EcoSport.
